{
  "name": "businessweek-stratus-launch-fail-safe-ba-82c028",
  "title": "A Fail-Safe Entry That's a Bargain (Stratus Computer launch coverage)",
  "description": "BusinessWeek's 16 November 1981 launch feature on Stratus Computer Inc. as a fail-safe-computing competitor to Tandem. Quotes Stratus president William E. Foster, IDC consultant John C. Hart, Cupertino consultant David E. Gold, ADL's Norman S. Zimbel, Tandem software-VP Dennis L. McEvoy, IVP managing partner Reid W. Dennis, and Dataquest's Richard J. Matlack. Establishes Stratus's $148K starting price vs Tandem's ~$264K, projects $5B fault-tolerant market by 1985, and notes Tandem's 142% three-year sales CAGR to $109M in 1980. Pre-Aberdeen industry-context artifact (Aberdeen founded 1988); Kastner joined Stratus in early 1980s as a marketing/sales-support hire \u2014 this story covers the era and company that became formative for him.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-04-25",
